<title>Fela Sowande, Nigerian Composer, Organist & Professor</title>
<meta name="description" content="Fela Sowande (1905-1987) was a pioneering Nigerian composer of jazz and classical music, an organist and a professor.  His biographer, Olobode Omojola, calls him the &quot;Father of modern Nigerian Art Music&quot;. Sowande was one of the first African composers to employ both traditional and Western classical forms of music. Among his best-known works are &quot;Nigerian Folk Symphony&quot; and &quot;African Suite&quot;.  &quot;African Suite&quot; is found on a CD, CBC Records SMCD 5135 (1994). ">
<meta name="keywords" content="African composer, African organist, African professor, African suite, Nigerian Folk Symphony, Father of Nigerian Art Music">
